HEADWORD: Reim
<hw>Reim</hw> <pr>(r?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>riem</ets>,
akin to G <ets>riemen</ets>; CF. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/ a towing line.]</ety>
<def>A strip of oxhide, deprived of hair, and rendered pliable, -- used
for twisting into ropes, etc.</def> <mark>[South Africa]</mark>
